{"id":"mai-tyib","kind":"ticket","type":"task","title":"Review: session 2026-03-28 full diff","tags":["review"],"body":"## 1. Change Explanation\n\nThis range adds four big pieces of behavior:\n\n| Area | Files | What changed |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| CRDT text engine | `pkg/crdt/*`, `pkg/crdt/yrs-wasi/src/lib.rs`, `go.mod`, `vendor/github.com/sergi/go-diff/*` | Added diff-to-ops support and updated YDoc loading/merge behavior. |\n| Docs sync + note engine | `pkg/notes/docs.go`, `pkg/notes/engine.go`, `pkg/notes/fold.go`, `pkg/notes/index.go`, `pkg/notes/types.go` | Added `ydoc` state, comment-edit overlay, batch note rebuild, and CRDT-based doc sync. |\n| CLI and daemon | `cmd/mai/main.go`, `cmd/mai/commands.go`, `cmd/mai/lattice.go`, `cmd/mai/daemon*.go` | Added flag overhaul, `adr`, `priority`, `title`, `type`, `edit`, `doctor --purge`, dry-run docs sync, and background file watching. |\n| Tests/docs | `test/docs*.go`, `README.md`, `docs/crdt-wiring.plan.md` | Added broad docs-sync coverage and the CRDT wiring plan used by this session. |\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart LR\n    CLI[mai edit / mai docs sync / daemon] --\u003e Sync[docs + engine wiring]\n    Sync --\u003e Body[body events]\n    Sync --\u003e YDoc[ydoc events]\n    Disk[materialized .md file] \u003c--\u003e Sync\n    Body --\u003e Fold[folded note state]\n    YDoc --\u003e Fold\n```\n\n### Issue/Task Coverage Analysis\n\n**Source**: `docs/crdt-wiring.plan.md` lines 107-113 plus the review brief in `tic-pxey`\n\n| Requirement | Status | Evidence |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Add YDoc state to doc notes and fold it | ✅ Implemented | `pkg/notes/engine.go:174-179`, `pkg/notes/fold.go:147-151`, `pkg/notes/types.go:101-106` |\n| Use CRDT merge in `SyncDocs` when file and note diverge | ✅ Implemented | `pkg/notes/docs.go:105-133`, `pkg/notes/docs.go:337-389` |\n| When only the note changed, materialize the note/YDoc back to disk | ❌ Missing | `pkg/notes/engine.go:747-756` returns early on the first note-side body edit |\n| Preserve non-maitake frontmatter fields | ❌ Missing | `pkg/notes/docs.go:237-242` rewrites frontmatter from scratch |\n| Keep closed docs on disk and mark them closed in frontmatter | ❌ Missing | `pkg/notes/docs.go:169-177`, `pkg/notes/engine.go:742-744` still delete files |\n\n**Coverage verdict**: 2 requirements implemented, 3 requirements still missing.\n\n## 2. Suggest Fixing\n\n### [High] note-side doc edits no longer materialize to disk in auto-sync mode\n- Files: `pkg/notes/engine.go:307-313`, `pkg/notes/engine.go:727-756`\n- `Append(...Field:\"body\")` always calls `autoSyncDoc(fullID)`. `autoSyncDoc` then reads the existing file and bails out whenever `existingBody != state.Body`.\n- After `mai edit \u003cdoc-id\u003e`, the file still contains the old body, so the hashes necessarily differ and the function returns without writing. In plain language: the first note-side body edit makes auto-sync stop working until someone runs `mai docs sync`.\n- This misses the plan requirement \"When only note changed: materialize YDoc.Content() to file.\"\n- Fix: compare the on-disk body with the **previous synced note body**, not with the just-updated state. A stored last-sync hash/body would make this explicit.\n\n### [High] sync writes destroy Obsidian frontmatter\n- Files: `pkg/notes/docs.go:237-242`, `docs/crdt-wiring.plan.md:109-113`, `test/docs_adversarial_test.go:364-385`\n- `writeDocFile` rewrites every file as only `mai-id` plus body, so `title`, `tags`, `aliases`, `cssclasses`, `date`, and any other Obsidian frontmatter are dropped on the first write/update/import.\n- The plan explicitly says only `mai-id` should be touched and other frontmatter must be preserved.\n- The added test named `TestDocs_ExtraFrontmatterPreserved` does not actually assert preservation; it only checks that `mai-id` and body exist, so it gives false confidence.\n- Fix: parse the frontmatter block, update only maitake-owned keys, and write the untouched user keys back out.\n\n### [High] closed doc notes still delete files instead of marking them closed\n- Files: `pkg/notes/docs.go:169-177`, `pkg/notes/engine.go:742-744`, `docs/crdt-wiring.plan.md:109-113`\n- The plan says closed docs should stay on disk and gain `closed: true` in frontmatter so Obsidian does not throw a delete modal. The implementation still does `os.Remove` in both the batch sync path and auto-sync path.\n- That is a requirements miss, not a style nit. Closing a doc still removes the materialized file entirely.\n- Fix: keep the file, update frontmatter with a maitake-owned closed flag, and teach sync/fold to treat that as presentation state rather than deletion.\n\n### [High] daemon tombstones normal editor saves\n- Files: `cmd/mai/daemon.go:105-108`, `cmd/mai/daemon.go:149-170`, `test/docs_daemon_fsnotify_test.go:113-171`\n- The daemon treats any `fsnotify.Remove` on a `.md` file as an intentional delete and immediately tombstones the note.\n- Many editors save by rename/remove/create. On those save paths, a normal save emits a remove-like event before the file reappears, so the daemon can tombstone a live doc just because the editor wrote atomically.\n- The skipped tests in `test/docs_daemon_fsnotify_test.go` already admit there are unresolved fsnotify recreate/rewrite races. This path makes those races destructive.\n- Fix: debounce delete handling too. Only tombstone after the path is still missing after a quiet period, and ignore remove/rename sequences that are followed by a recreate of the same path.\n\n## 3. Possible Simplifications\n\n- Collapse doc materialization into one helper that owns frontmatter merge, closed-state handling, and safe overwrite rules. Right now those rules are split across `SyncDocs`, `autoSyncDoc`, and daemon-triggered sync, which is why they disagree.\n- `lastSyncBody()` exists as a stub in `pkg/notes/docs.go:324-331` but the actual sync contract is duplicated elsewhere. Either implement it and use it everywhere, or delete the stub until the sync boundary is real.\n\n## 4. Consider Asking User\n\n- The plan says “closed doc stays on disk with `closed: true`”, but the shipped code deletes it. If the contract changed on purpose, the plan and tests need to be updated together. If not, the code should come back to the written plan before merge.\n\n## 5. Suggested Checks\n\n```bash\n# Full suite once Go is available in PATH\ngo test ./...\n\n# New regression: note-side doc edit must update the materialized file\ngo test ./test -run TestDocsSync_NoteEditUpdatesFile\n\n# New regression: extra frontmatter survives import + update\ngo test ./test -run TestDocs_ExtraFrontmatterPreserved\n\n# New regression: closing a doc keeps the file and sets closed:true\ngo test ./test -run TestDocs_CloseMarksFrontmatter\n\n# New regression: atomic-save editor sequence must not tombstone the note\ngo test ./test -run TestDaemon_AtomicSaveDoesNotTombstone\n```\n\n## 6. Task Summary\n\n- Reviewed `git diff c1c55a6..b4329ec`, with focus on `pkg/crdt`, `pkg/notes`, and `cmd/mai`.\n- The core CRDT wiring is moving in the right direction: YDoc state exists, diff/apply exists, and `SyncDocs` now has a merge path.\n- I could not run the Go test suite in this worker environment because `go test ./...` fails with `go: command not found`.\n- The blocking problems are not in the CRDT library itself; they are in the docs-sync contract around disk materialization and Obsidian compatibility. Three explicit plan requirements are still missing, and the daemon delete path adds a new destructive edge case.","timestamp":"2026-03-29T09:58:55Z","branch":"main"}
